## Pass 2: Narrative Strategy

### 2.1 Opening (Choose ONE)

| Strategy | Pattern | Best When |
|----------|---------|-----------|
| **Paradox** | "Technology exists to [X]â€”yet [reality]..." | Capability vs. reality gap |
| **Moment** | "In [date], [event] marked a turning point..." | Pivotal milestone |
| **Number** | "[Statistic]. That figure encapsulates..." | One stat crystallizes all |
| **Question** | "What happens when [A] collides with [B]?" | Collision course |
| **Stakes** | "[$X / Y people] will be affected..." | Quantified impact |

**Selection**: [Strategy] â€” [Why]

### 2.2 Structure (Choose ONE)

**Transformation Arc** â€” Before/after narrative
- Current State â†’ Forces of Change â†’ New Reality â†’ Path Forward

**Collision Course** â€” Competing forces
- Force A â†’ Force B â†’ Collision Point â†’ Winners/Losers

**Hidden Story** â€” Counterintuitive findings
- Surface Reality â†’ Evidence â†’ Real Story â†’ Implications

**Countdown** â€” Deadline-driven
- Deadline â†’ Stakes â†’ Who's Ready â†’ Who's Not â†’ Reckoning

**Evidence Mosaic** â€” Fallback when no dominant signal
- Landscape â†’ Patterns â†’ Outliers â†’ Implications

**Selection**: [Pattern] â€” [Why]

### 2.3 Closing (Choose ONE)

| Strategy | Pattern |
|----------|---------|
| **Callback** | Evolve opening |
| **Choice** | Binary decision, clear stakes |
| **Prediction** | Bold, sourced forecast |
| **Question** | What matters most |
| **Imperative** | Direct call to action |

**Selection**: [Strategy] â€” [Why]

